<br>
However, there is one thing we agree with.  This shouldn't air here.  Not because it is trash, but because it is simply not the place of a television network to teach our children tolerance.  The job of teaching children about things of this nature falls squarely on the shoulders of the childs guardian.  <br>
<br>
When have we as a society suddenly slipped into this mindset that it's ok for television to teach our kids about life?  S. Street was a place that kids could be entertained.  There is a vast difference between showing kids the ABCs and teaching HIV awareness.  That is a boundry that should never be crossed.  The boundry that crosses into the family's responsibility for teaching and educating children about tolerance.  <br>
<br>
This whole issue has nothing to do with liberals and conservatives.  It has everything to do with a television network trying to impede upon the rights of parents/guardians to teach and raise children the way they believe to be right.  And if there are people out there who are not comfortable talking to their children about these issues, and feel that TV will do the talking, what the hell are they doing with kids in the first place.  <br>
<br>
I truly feel as a parent that S. Street is going to far on this issue.  I take full responsibility with my kids to teach them about life.  I take special care to show them hatred is not a way to live life at all.  I do not tolerate racism in my house, nor will I tolerate bigotry of any kind.  It is my responsibility to teach what homosexuality is, what HIV/AIDS is, and the fact that one has nothing to do with the other.  I make sure that I know what i am talking about before I speak to them, so I know that I am giving them correct guidance.  No television show can ever compare to what a parent or guardian can offer.  And no guardian should ever rely on a muppet to teach this.  And no child at 3 years old should need to be taught this kind of lesson this early in life.  LET THEM BE KIDS FIRST!!!  Let them have their innocence for awhile.  <br>
<br>
Yes, I am a conservative.  I am not a racist, redneck, gun toting warmonger like alot of people try to make conservatives out to be.  Yes I listen to Rush, and no I don't agree with everything he says.  Having a mind of my own is a great thing.  I will love my children no matter what they become.  As long as I know they have are good people.  And no television show can teach someone to be a good person.<br>
